ve clerics at numbers 1 and 17, Betty who is number 1 is not online when Ragefire spawns, Wilma at number 17 cannot take her place in the rotation and kill Ragefire.<br><br>2. To have your name added to the list, you must have completed all other steps towards obtaining your epic and you must send a screenshot of you with the swirling pearl to saela@eqdrinal.com prior to being added. There are NO EXCEPTIONS to this rule. Along with the pearl screenshot, you should also send in (1) your e-mail address, (2) your guild's name, and (3) a list of persons who may be contacted if you are not online. The clerics who are currently on the list must send in this information to maintain their position on the list.<br><br>3. Always have someone in the RF camp, whether it be you or your representative. Anyone in the RF camp should refer clerics seeking to be added to the list to this forum.<br><br>4. There is a 3 hour time limit from the moment Ragefire spawns for the first cleric on the list to kill him, during which time other forces are welcome to gather and prepare, but not engage Ragefire. If the first cleric on the list does not kill Ragefire in this time, the list's integrity should continue to be maintained by going through the list in order until a cleric who is online is in the zone and ready. Ragefire is never FFA -- after three hours, that spawn belongs to the highest listed cleric prepared for an engagement.<br><br>5. Post here immediately after you have killed RF so that the next person on the list is notified.<br><br>6. Those clerics with * in front of their name have sent in their screenshots showing them with the swirling pearl from Sol B.<br><br><br>This list was created to maintain civility among the guilds of Drinal. The current listing is:<br><br>1 *Chindra (Unconquered) <br>2 *Castironn (House Bloodthorne) <br>3 *Funno (Guardians of the Keep) <br>4 *Koll (Bushido Clain) <br>5 *Saela (The Kindred) <br>6 *Dolphine (Undivided Faith) <br>7 *Laline (no guild) <br>8 *Gigelat (Guardians of the Keep) <br>9 *Sdari (no guild) <br>10 *Salanii (Undivided Faith) <br>11 *Reeko (SoulBonded) <br>12 *Ferhere (Dragon Reborn) <br>13 *Myrkul (Unconquered) <br>14 *Sraiye (Mystic Legacy) <br>15 *Exidus (Blood Honor) <br>16 *Oakiey (Guardians of the Keep) <br>17 *Bowlem (Dragon Reborn) <br>18 *Tpar (Lords of the Ters'tai) <br>19 *Racknar (Guardians of the Keep) <br><br>What this means, in general, is that when I am the cleric that is up to camp ragefire, (and in fact when I&quot;m next in line) I would ask that the following happen:<br><br>1)  Any guild raids plans be suspended pending the camp;<br>2)  That we immediately begin to plan people being available on a moment's notice to kill ragefire;<br><br>My alternates for this are Baledor and Kyrra; they have the means and knowledge to contact me and will assist also.<br><br>It would be a great source of pride for the Lords of the Ters'Tai to have a cleric epic, and I hope you will assist me in this final prize.<br><br>In service to you all,<br><br> <p><br><center><font size=5 color=red>Tpar a'Nerriap<br></font><font size=4 color=blue><b>High Priest of Mithaniel Marr<br>Elder Lord of the Ters'Tai<br></font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/udamonius.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Damonius</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://baiinc.com/images/dragon5.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Earl Marshall</span><br>  Posts: 159<br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/16/02 9:00:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/flottdrinalfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=612.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: RAGEFIRE CAMP AND CLERIC EPIC</span><hr size=1> I will definately assist. What is the spawn rate for Ragefire? Are we looking at days, or weeks for your